{"id":14881355,"mediaExerciseId":"1dd0ddf4-df5b-4bdd-ad25-b651b762ea94","exerciseName":"9","chapterName":"12","chapterTitle":"Some Lessons From Capital Market History","groupId":612363,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":416,"solutions":[{"id":6218990,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we need to solve for the average return as well as the variance and standard deviation for these returns. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**a.** In order to solve for the average return, we can simply divide the sum of all returns by the number of years. In this case, we have:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Arithmetic average return}&=\\dfrac{8-15+19+31+21}{5}\\\\\n&=12.8\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe arithmetic average return for this stock is $12.8\\%$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**b.** In order to solve for the variance, we can use this formula:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\sigma^2&=\\dfrac{\\sum(\\text{X}-\\text{Average})}{\\text{n}-1}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere X is the value for the return and n is the number of years.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Substituting the values, we will get:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\sigma^2&=\\dfrac{(8-12.8)^2+(-15-12.8)^2+(19-12.8)^2+(31-12.8)^2+(21-12.8)^2}{4}\\\\[15 pt]\n&=308.2\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe variance for the returns is $308.2$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"In order to get the standard deviation, we can simply take the square root of the variance. \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\sigma&=\\sqrt{308.2}\\\\[15 pt]\n&=17.56\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe standard deviation is $17.56\\%$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"b69f3cf3-1978-47d3-9c26-827985d5b78c","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881356,"exerciseName":"10","page":416,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"84fa068e-f247-45a2-8405-575c80b01c4c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-questions-and-problems-10-84fa068e-f247-45a2-8405-575c80b01c4c"},{"id":14881357,"exerciseName":"11","page":416,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"fe715792-39a3-4af5-97da-83ee5c3f5b84","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-questions-and-problems-11-fe715792-39a3-4af5-97da-83ee5c3f5b84"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881354,"exerciseName":"8","page":416,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"2f56f094-2c38-4394-a5ae-3749e94a4241","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-questions-and-problems-8-2f56f094-2c38-4394-a5ae-3749e94